---

## What Was Rebranded

| What | Before | After |
|---|---|---|
| Package name | `amplitude-js` | `acai-js` |
| Main class | `AmplitudeClient` | `AcaiClient` |
| Server zone export | `AmplitudeServerZone` | `AcaiServerZone` |
| Cookie prefix | `amp` | `acai` |
| localStorage keys | `amplitude_unsent`, `amplitude_sessionId`, etc. | `acai_unsent`, `acai_sessionId`, etc. |
| Event server URL | `api.amplitude.com` | `api.acai.yourdomain.com` ← **you set this** |
| Attribution event | `[Amplitude] Attribution Captured` | `[Acai] Attribution Captured` |
| Library name in payloads | `amplitude-js` | `acai-js` |

---

## Steps to Go Live

**1. Stand up your collector server** (Node/Express, Go, Python — anything):
```js
app.post('/2/httpapi', (req, res) => {
  const { api_key, events } = req.body;
  // store events in your DB
  res.json({ code: 200, events_ingested: events.length });
});
```

**2. Set your server URL** in `src/constants.js`:
```js
EVENT_LOG_URL: 'api.acai.yourdomain.com',  // ← replace with your real host
```

**3. Build the SDK:**
```bash
yarn install
yarn build
# outputs: acai.js, acai.esm.js, acai.umd.js, acai.min.js
```

**4. Host `acai.min.js`** on your CDN or as an npm package.

**5. Users track events like this:**
```js
import acai from 'acai-js';
acai.init('YOUR_API_KEY', null, { apiEndpoint: 'api.acai.yourdomain.com' });
acai.logEvent('button_clicked', { label: 'Sign Up' });
```

**6. Push to GitHub** and optionally publish to npm:
```bash
cd acai-js
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/acai-js
git push -u origin master
npm publish  # if you want it on npm
```
